{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rancid-vane-wreak","description":"Each plan-review workflow op independently re-assembles the entire ticket graph from the store, so one gate run does ~4×(1 + 1 + K children) `show_ticket`/`list_tickets` reads. On an epic with many children this is the latency the observability commit (`08cd4c325`) was added to explain — \"a slow epic review looks like a hang\" — a client-facing reliability/perceived-performance issue.\n\n## Why\nThe B-RETIRE migration decomposed the review into pure `uses` ops but gave them no shared context, so each re-reads + re-derives the graph (`orchestrator.assemble_context` is itself an N+1 read: `show_ticket` + `list_tickets(parent=)` + one `show_ticket` per child).\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py:66,147,212,235` — the precheck/assemble/verify_inputs/coach_inputs ops each call `orchestrator.assemble_context(...)`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/production_batch_runner.py:85` and `__init__.py:108` — assemble again.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py:77-110` — `assemble_context` (the N+1 read).\nApproach: assemble `PlanContext` ONCE in `plan_review_precheck`, serialize its `state`/`children` into the precheck step outputs, and have downstream ops reconstruct `PlanContext` from those outputs (as `plan_review_coach` already does at `workflow_ops.py:342`). Alternatively memoize on `(run_id, ticket_id)`.\n\n## Scope\nIn: eliminate the redundant re-reads within one gate run; preserve verdict bytes exactly. Out: changing the verdict/finding shape or the workflow YAML's op sequence.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A single plan-review gate run assembles the ticket graph at most once (assert via the observability step counts / a read-counter spy).\n- [ ] Verdict output is byte-identical to pre-change for a fixed fixture (characterization test).\n- [ ] Measured store reads for an epic-with-K-children review drop from ~4×(2+K) to ~(2+K).\n- [ ] Existing plan-review tests pass.","id":"9d34-bfcd-54c3-4e7a","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":2,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Eliminate redundant ticket-graph re-assembly in plan-review gate"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605234072316001,"uuid":"6f88d3e6-13bd-46f4-87f7-b0e499f08533"}